71 Sections 24 and 32 of this bill revise certain procedures for the judicial review of
72 the decision of an appeals officer.
73 If a claim for a period of temporary total disability is allowed, existing law
74 requires an industrial insurer to make the first payment within 14 working days
75 after receipt of the initial certification of disability, and regularly thereafter. (NRS
76 616C.475) Section 27 of this bill establishes the same requirements for payment
77 when a claim for a period of temporary partial disability is allowed.
78 Existing law authorizes hearing officers and appeals officers, under certain
79 circumstances, to allow discovery by deposition or interrogatories according to the
80 Nevada Rules of Civil Procedure. (NRS 616D.050, 616D.090) Sections 28 and 29
81 of this bill prohibit a hearing officer from allowing such discovery, and revise
82 provisions governing the circumstances under which an appeals officer may allow
83 discovery.
84 Existing law sets forth certain procedures for appealing a final determination
85 concerning accident benefits made by an organization for managed care. (NRS
86 616C.305) Existing law requires, for a determination of the percentage of disability
87 resulting from occupational disease of the heart or lungs, that the determination be
88 made jointly by the attending physician and examining physician of a claimant, or,
89 under certain circumstances, a designated third physician or panel of physicians.
90 (NRS 616C.459) Section 34 of this bill repeals those procedures and requirements,
91 and sections 15, 16, 18, 19, 21-23, 26 and 31 of this bill make conforming changes
92 to remove references to those procedures and requirements from existing law.
